ej,stane101,M,conlj102,Obstruction call ej,riced101,P,conlj102,Obstruction call (Threw glove) $Solly Hemus dove to his right for the hard-hit grounder; $Jackie Robinson fell over Hemus as he sprawled in the base path; 3B umpire Tom Gorman ruled obstruction on Hemus and allowed Robinson to score; Del Rice ran to 3B to argue with Gorman and Cardinals Manager Eddie Stanky tried to get between them; Rice and Stanky ejected by HP umpire Jocko Conlan; Stanky played the game under protest for what he called a 'misinterpretation of the rules;' no error was charged to Hemus1953BRO.EVN.regular.comment.csv"
